<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFF86A47FD1F956C1B27BF59" pageId="3" pageNumber="761" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFF86A47FD1F956C1B27BF59" blockId="3.[738,1331,747,1170]" pageId="3" pageNumber="761">
Previously placed in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFF86A47FBE9956C1A90B864" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1819" box="[1045,1168,821,854]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nycticeius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="761" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Nycticeius</taxonomicName>
, S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFF86A47FB30956C1B33B864" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1876" box="[1228,1331,821,854]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="761" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pallidus">pallidus</taxonomicName>
was transferred to Scotoecusas its only Asian member by J. E. Hill in 1974. In 1942, G. H. H. Tate suggested that the name noctulinus, introduced by I. Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire in 1834, might be an earlier name for the species, but until this is validated the name 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFF86A47FCC492131D9FBF59" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1876" box="[824,927,1098,1131]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="761" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pallidus">pallidus</taxonomicName>
is here retained. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
